<doc f='llvm/polly/lib/External/isl/imath/imrat.h' l='182'>/** Converts `r` to a zero-terminated string of the format `&quot;n/d&quot;` with `n` and
    `d` in the specified radix and writing no more than `limit` bytes to the
    given output buffer `str`. The output of the numerator includes a sign flag
    if `r` is negative.  Requires `MP_MIN_RADIX &lt;= radix &lt;= MP_MAX_RADIX`. */</doc>
